  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_1255819994" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1255819994" />
    <a title="Wendy&#39;sThoughts" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17755575-wendy-sthoughts"><img alt="Wendy&#39;sThoughts" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1378340325p2/17755575.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1255819994?book_show_action=true">Apr 15, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Wendy&#39;sThoughts" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Wendy&#39;sThoughts" href="/user/show/17755575-wendy-sthoughts">Wendy&#39;sThoughts</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Tattooed Musicians, Second Chance Love, Romance</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1255819994" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14118898531409673749"><b>4.5 Finding Each Other Again Stars<br/>* * * * 1/2<br/>Growing up is hard...throw in grade school/high school clicks with cliches and you have a perfect storm for teenagers making bad choices...There is just no getting around it. Doesn&apos;t matter economically or regionally...if the circumstances happen when people feel their only way to prove themselves is to take some type of control...whether positively or not...they will. These notions are part of this excellent book, Forever Red.<br/><br/>I want to do a side note</b></span>
  <span id="freeText14118898531409673749" style="display:none"><b>4.5 Finding Each Other Again Stars<br>* * * * 1/2<br>Growing up is hard...throw in grade school/high school clicks with cliches and you have a perfect storm for teenagers making bad choices...There is just no getting around it. Doesn't matter economically or regionally...if the circumstances happen when people feel their only way to prove themselves is to take some type of control...whether positively or not...they will. These notions are part of this excellent book, Forever Red.<br><br>I want to do a side note, first. I have been so lucky lately reading so many over 4 star reads. Seriously, The Book Gods have blessed me. It is not that I am easy....well, maybe my name has been on a few bathroom walls......NOT! No, I have just had a selection of reads which have touched all the bases for me and this book did as well.<br><br>You have the perfect set up for a book to go very wrong - wrong side of the track girl meets right side of track guy.</b> Girl and her friends have been taking control of their being on the "wrong side" by manipulating guys for fun and games... rather than losing their hearts. Their reputations are crap...and for the most part justified. Enter new guy...and for the first time ever, Lia, our main character feels something for him. <br><br>Our new guy has a very interesting background which connects with our girl. It comes out after they start to be tentative friends, he comes from a Country Music legacy. He doesn't make a big ta-do about it... but our girl was a huge fan of his grandfather and this love and understanding binds them even closer. <br><br>Neil, the new kid, has it all going for him...football player, musician, artist and kind of an old soul...who learned how to love and care about things from his Gramps. It made him see things others didn't. It made him be more accepting of the young wonder he met... the girl who was honest didn't lie to him or suck up. She was a real person he could be himself with. <br><br>We read of their love story... of how they grow into this couple no one understands...and how past mistakes in judgment can color how people will manipulate non-negative behavior to fit their plans...like jealous teenage girls or even singularly focused parents. <br>These two special teenagers who see their love as real...are put to the test...and unfortunately due to assumptions, true love for one another and no communication...a massive decision is made by our girl...hurting the one person she loved.<br><br>Twelve years pass and Lia has been following Neil's career...Neil, however, was never to find Lia no matter how hard he tried. He is bitter; has written songs about his pain and lived the life of a famous sexy musician...meaning lots of nameless sex. All of his band members plus family know he has never gotten over Lia...and they wish he would just move on.<br><br>Lia is turning 30 and her friends are taking her for a surprise trip. She finds out it is to have VIP tickets and meetings with Nate Kelly who she knew as Neil. Her friends have no idea of the connection; Lia reinvented herself after leaving everyone behind. She finds herself locked in a room with crazed fans for him in a meet and greet...looking for a way to escape. Heading for the back door she walks straight into him...Neil is as shocked as Lia and cannot deal with this as the show is about to start. Their old friend from high school, Mike, now works as security for Neil takes her to the side after the show and there Neil pulls Lia aside into an empty room. Both are stunned and after the shock wears off...Neil kisses her...both know this isn't done...the embers still burn bright under all the inflicted pain...<br><br>This story is told in two parts. In the High school time, we get the whole experience and it flows through all the stages in their maturing as teenagers. We get to feel it all perfectly. We understand all the point of views because it switches from his to hers. We feel for them when they are separated by parental scorn. We see how outside forces work to instill doubt...and we see how crazy in love Neil is for Lia.<br><br>We also see how Lia understands her past mistakes and owns them fully. She learns how what she was doing was not accomplishing what she thought it was...it seemed she and her friends had control... but in the end... their actions and the results of them were what had the control and she worked to grow from it.<br><br>In the second half of the book, we see these two work at re-meeting the people they were, what the assumption of who they seemed to be and finally getting to know the real adult them. They still have cliches and knee jerk reactions to fight...Lia still needs to not hold back with Neil and sometimes that was a bit of an issue for me... But this all worked itself out and not in a long drawn out way.<br><br>An additional plus with this was all of the secondary characters. We had them all and they brought the goods to the table. The best friends... the bandmates ...Neil's sister and brother...even the bitchy parents. All of them held their own and contributed.<br><br>This book is worth the read. If you love Second Chances... this is your book. If you love a bit of forbidden, it is there too. If you just love a great love story which is over the years and meant to be... this is your tale...and having the main guy be a hunk and grow into a tattooed, pierced award-winning Rock Country star doesn't hurt either.<br><br>I am sure there are going to be more books with the secondary characters in the future...we are primed for them... and please do not make me wait too long... I want more of the 'Bama Boys! <br><br><b>~~~ Before Reading ~~~</b><br><b>Second Chance Love- Check!<br><br>Country Music Industry - Check!<br><br>Fingers crossed, it is Go Time :D</b><br><br><i>A gifted copy was provided by author/publisher for an honest review.</i><br> <br><strong>For more Reviews, Free E-books and Giveaways</strong><br><div>
  <br>
  <a href="http://starangelsreviews.blogspot.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">
    <img alt=" photo banner_zpsb3ab83a0.jpg" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1407612151i/10746470._SX540_.jpg" width="400" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
  </a>
</div></span>
  <a data-text-id="14118898531409673749" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

