        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1253651629" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13410188052598100691"><b>*** LOVED THIS !! ***</b><br/><br/><b>STORY OF LIA AND NEIL...</b><br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1429042307i/14520910.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1429042307i/14520911._SY540_.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>This is a story told in two parts...<br/><br/>It starts when LIA and NEIl are just teenagers.I&apos;m normally not one for college romances ( which part one is ) but it TOTALLY worked for me,in fact it more than worked as I actually enjoyed part one the most.LIA is a lot different to the sterotypical college girl...she comes from the wrong side of the tracks,thinks people think less of her, and her and two friends play a dangerous game....they set their sites on a c</span>
  <span id="freeText13410188052598100691" style="display:none"><b>*** LOVED THIS !! ***</b><br><br><b>STORY OF LIA AND NEIL...</b><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1429042307i/14520910.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1429042307i/14520911._SY540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>This is a story told in two parts...<br><br>It starts when LIA and NEIl are just teenagers.I'm normally not one for college romances ( which part one is ) but it TOTALLY worked for me,in fact it more than worked as I actually enjoyed part one the most.LIA is a lot different to the sterotypical college girl...she comes from the wrong side of the tracks,thinks people think less of her, and her and two friends play a dangerous game....they set their sites on a certain boy or man and compete to see who can seduce him first....<br>Enter NEIL, the new kid in school...they develop a strong friendship which turns to young love...<br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1429042307i/14520912.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>LIA' s past comes back to haunt her and she walks away from NEIL<br><br><b>PART TWO TAKES PLACE 12 YEARS LATER..</b><br><br>LIA has built a new life but has followed NEIL'S career as a Country Singer...her friends arrange to take her to one of his concerts not knowing their past...<br>They re connect but secrets threaten their relationship.This is a lovely story of second chance love spanning over many years ( something I love ).The writing flows beautifully and I could not put it down.Some great secondary characters...especially loved Mike.I adored the Epilogue but must admit I had pretty much worked it out...<br><br>First book by this Author and it definitely won't be the last!!!</span>
