<div id="review_1322307710" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1322307710" />
    <a title="mich" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/17575003-mich"><img alt="mich" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1361178507p2/17575003.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1322307710?book_show_action=true">Jun 30, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="mich" class="user" itemprop="url" name="mich" href="/user/show/17575003-mich">mich</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25333776-forever-red">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17575003-mich?shelf=yeah-i-skimmed-so-sue-me">yeah-i-skimmed-so-sue-me</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17575003-mich?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17575003-mich?shelf=started-good-but-went-downhill">started-good-but-went-downhill</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17575003-mich?shelf=kindle-unlimited">kindle-unlimited</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/17575003-mich?shelf=rocker-music-romance">rocker-music-romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1322307710" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16170465755558546726">This book combined three of my favorite things in the contemporary genre! Best friends to lovers, reunion/second chances and musician-romance (that&apos;s the trifecta of awesome right there!) The setup isn&apos;t bad, despite it being premised on that oft used, nauseatingly stupid &quot;I&apos;m doing this hurtful thing to you because I love you and you&apos;re better off without me&quot; bullshit.<br/><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>I had thought I was so mature, that somehow I had all the answers and knew what was best for everyone, so I made their d</i></b></blockquote></span>
  <span id="freeText16170465755558546726" style="display:none">This book combined three of my favorite things in the contemporary genre! Best friends to lovers, reunion/second chances and musician-romance (that's the trifecta of awesome right there!) The setup isn't bad, despite it being premised on that oft used, nauseatingly stupid "I'm doing this hurtful thing to you because I love you and you're better off without me" bullshit.<br /><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>I had thought I was so mature, that somehow I had all the answers and knew what was best for everyone, so I made their decisions for them.</i>
  </b>
</blockquote><br />So you know what I was thinking right? Oh great, <i>this</i> tired-ass crap again? BUT! But then, pretty much immediately, we get this:<br /><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>In reality, I was just a naive, small-town girl with more fashion sense than common sense - and looking back at the pictures proves that I didn't know fashion for shit.</i>
  </b>
</blockquote> I knew right then that Lia was gonna be my kinda girl, and settled in for what I thought would be a really great read.<br /><br />Actually, it ended up being pretty meh. The book is split up with the beginning half chronicling their high school years and the later half follows them when they reunite in their early thirties. I enjoyed the first half, although I did feel like it was really draggy at times (there's just way too many details and too many unimportant events that are mentioned. Seriously, this book is too long - a little snippy snippy throughout the whole thing would have done wonders.) <br /><br />The second half kinda killed things for me. To me, this should've been the <i>better</i> half. As adults, I thought Neil's and Lia's story would be taken to a higher level -- the stakes would be higher, the drama more intense, the sexy times steamier. Instead, the reunion felt anticlimactic, the romance bordered on cheesy, and the drama was very tame and frankly, pretty boring. This had potential to be really good, if only the story had been....I dunno, <i>more.</i> More, like <i>what</i>, you ask? How the hell should I know, I'm not a writer! But as a reader, I just know that I wanted WAY more than what I got. <br /><br /><b>2.5 stars</b> The writing was decent and I'd try something again from this author.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16170465755558546726" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


