        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1629201007" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2423885692137351907">I couldn&apos;t put this one down.<br/><br/>A second chance romance featuring childhood first loves all grown up. I was hooked from the prologue where our 29 year-old Lia is all set to go on a surprise meet and greet with hawt country music megastar, Nate. Except Nate was her first love who she ran away from age 18. Love that set up.<br/><br/>This is narrated in alternate fp, initially ten years ago and then now. It&apos;s hard for me to get into a love story when I know it&apos;s going to go tits up, I&apos;m kind of reading with one</span>
  <span id="freeText2423885692137351907" style="display:none">I couldn't put this one down.<br /><br />A second chance romance featuring childhood first loves all grown up. I was hooked from the prologue where our 29 year-old Lia is all set to go on a surprise meet and greet with hawt country music megastar, Nate. Except Nate was her first love who she ran away from age 18. Love that set up.<br /><br />This is narrated in alternate fp, initially ten years ago and then now. It's hard for me to get into a love story when I know it's going to go tits up, I'm kind of reading with one foot still on the ground, not quite all in. What I loved though was that less than half of the book was set in the past then we moved forward to now, there's no skipping around.<br /><br />Add in the best friend, her bitchy friends, his difficult mother and lots of sexual chemistry and I was hooked. Nate made me swoon.<br /><br />Complete story but there's more in the series featuring different characters. Loved this, recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2423885692137351907" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
