    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1254099256" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1254099256" />
    <a title="Jean" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25860981-jean"><img alt="Jean" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1458327401p2/25860981.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1254099256?book_show_action=true">Apr 13, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jean" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jean" href="/user/show/25860981-jean">Jean</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/25860981-jean?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1254099256" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3821342363392101652">Well, I was looking for a country rock star book, and I found it (thanks to a recommendation from Niki), and I loved it! <br/><br/>This book had everything I love.....friends to lovers romance, a strong heroine, an amazing hero, angst, bitchy women, family drama, trauma, separation, friendship, hope, and that long awaited reunion which was well worth the wait!!  Second chance romance is exactly what this book is about!<br/><br/>Lia (Cecelia) is from a poor family and only wants to get out of her small town.  Neil/N</span>
  <span id="freeText3821342363392101652" style="display:none">Well, I was looking for a country rock star book, and I found it (thanks to a recommendation from Niki), and I loved it! <br /><br />This book had everything I love.....friends to lovers romance, a strong heroine, an amazing hero, angst, bitchy women, family drama, trauma, separation, friendship, hope, and that long awaited reunion which was well worth the wait!!  Second chance romance is exactly what this book is about!<br /><br />Lia (Cecelia) is from a poor family and only wants to get out of her small town.  Neil/Nate (there is an explanation for the name) is new in town and immediately drawn to Lia.  They become great friends and I loved the banter between them.  Eventually, it becomes clear that they have strong feelings for each other.  When things spin out of control at the most inopportune moment, Lia runs.....she runs so far that no one can find her.....especially Neil.  She does remain friends with his friend, Mike, though and asks that he not tell Neil anything.  Even though there was some drama before Lia left, her real reason for leaving was so that she would not hold Neil back from his future life.....a life that appeared to look better without Lia, in Lia's opinion anyway.  Neil moves on and his life explodes into super stardom, which made it easy for Lia to keep tabs on him.  However, he had no clue where she was, what she was doing, who she was with, or even if she was even alive....I felt really bad for him! <br /><br />I hate when couples separate for years......and I mean it was years!!!!  Like 15 years!!  Ugh!!  That hurts my heart so much....I always feel like they've wasted so much time when they could have been spending it together happy!<br /><br />When she unexpectedly shows up at one of his concerts that her friend won tickets to with a meet and greet with the band, the sh!t hits the fan!<br /> <br />Anyway, I LOVED this book!!  I could not put it down!  First book for me by Carina Adams and I highly recommend it!  Of course, I'm a City Girl with a Country Heart so I was excited to read about a "country rock star" for a change!! I loved the band members! They were hysterical!<br /><br /><b>
  <i>OH, OH, OH, AND THAT EPILOGUE!!!!!  WHOA.......WTF!!  MIKE'S POV.....THAT JUST THREW ME FOR A LOOP!!!!!!!!  THERE HAS GOT TO BE A FOLLOW-UP TO THIS BOOK OR I WILL DIE!!!!<b></b><i></i></i>
</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="3821342363392101652" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


