<div id="review_1250436893" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1250436893" />
    <a title="Candi~Dirty Laundry Review" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16537005-candi-dirty-laundry-review"><img alt="Candi~Dirty Laundry Review" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1477705139p2/16537005.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1250436893?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Candi~Dirty Laundry Review" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Candi~Dirty Laundry Review" href="/user/show/16537005-candi-dirty-laundry-review">Candi~Dirty Laundry Review</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1250436893" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15901971590303642720">OMG OMG OMG THIS BOOK!!<br/><br/>It gave me all the feels! And so much more! It’s not often that I’m offered an arc, and of an author that I have not read before, and than completely knocks me on my butt. It’s rare that gems like these land in my hand. Ones, that I just want to scream from the rooftops “READ THIS BOOK!!!” And this book was like striking gold.<br/><br/>It’s written in 2 parts. Which makes it long. And for $2.99, i think it’s way underpriced. IMO. But this was done perfectly. You needed that “back th</span>
  <span id="freeText15901971590303642720" style="display:none">OMG OMG OMG THIS BOOK!!<br /><br />It gave me all the feels! And so much more! It’s not often that I’m offered an arc, and of an author that I have not read before, and than completely knocks me on my butt. It’s rare that gems like these land in my hand. Ones, that I just want to scream from the rooftops “READ THIS BOOK!!!” And this book was like striking gold.<br /><br />It’s written in 2 parts. Which makes it long. And for $2.99, i think it’s way underpriced. IMO. But this was done perfectly. You needed that “back then” back story, to fully grasp and appreciate the “now” part. It was done brilliantly. <br /><br />Part 1 goes back to high school. Where we go through Lia’s journey. She’s a young high schooler with a feisty sexual attitude. She’s not your typical teenage girl. And she knows this. But. She owns it. <br /><br />Enter one Neil/Nate Kelly. New to the small town and to the school. From his first day there. He is almost instantly taken by Lia. She has motives of her own. But those are quickly washed away after getting to know Neil. As with every typical high school it’s filled with mean girls, girls that are supposed to be your best friends, drama, rumors, angst, love, romance, heartache and heartbreak. And than the graduation dinner. Everything changes. Which brings us to book 2. The “Now”. I’d like to point out that Neil Kelly as a teenage boy is downright swoon worthy. Sweet, hot, caring. A good ole country boy from Alabama. Absolute perfection. But during the 12 year time span. Neil becomes Nate Kelly. The biggest country singer. The hottest. The baddest. The sexiest. With the tattoos and piercings all included. Good lord. We go from swoon worthy to down right panty melting. Side note. He has easily made a place in my top BBF list. Like, at the top of the list. <br /><br />Lia and Nate rediscover each other through all the ups and downs. They live two completely different worlds now but that don’t stop them. And through this journey is where I was completely swept away. Not just with Nate. But with all the characters from this story. The band members. Lia’s best friends. Mike. Sweet sweet mike. I loved them all. This book also had plenty of laugh out loud moments too. Which is a favorite of mine. The banter between them all. Like I said. Absolute perfection.<br />And then. The ending. The epilogue. Good god. It was a shocker. Not so much a Cliffy. But, just one of those moments that have you going “WTF!! I DID NOT SEE THAT COMING!!” <br /><br />I don’t want to give to much away. I will say that this is easily one of my favorite reads not just of 2015. But, ever. Seriously. This book just sucked me in. Again. It’s long. But not once did I stray or lose interest. Instead I kept saying I don’t want it to end!! Carina Adams. You are an amazing writer. I am in awe! And I can’t wait to see what you write next!!!<br /><br />If you haven’t yet. Go 1-click the hell out of this now!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="15901971590303642720" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


