<div id="review_1251713690" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1251713690" />
    <a title="Tangerine" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13808649-tangerine"><img alt="Tangerine" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613281772p2/13808649.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1251713690?book_show_action=true">Apr 10, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tangerine" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tangerine" href="/user/show/13808649-tangerine">Tangerine</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1251713690" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3906728555983138066"><br/><br/>3.5-4 STARS<br/><br/><br/>I picked this book up at random. I didn&apos;t read the blurb and I didn&apos;t read any reviews for it. All I knew was the title and what the cover looked like. It looks like I&apos;m going to have to do this more often seeing as I really enjoyed this one!<br/><br/>This was an enjoyable second chance romance. I have found that second chance romances really aren&apos;t my thing but this one worked. I loved how it was written in two parts. You got Nate and Lia&apos;s past and then their present. I enjoyed all of the sec</span>
  <span id="freeText3906728555983138066" style="display:none"><br /><br />3.5-4 STARS<br /><br /><br />I picked this book up at random. I didn't read the blurb and I didn't read any reviews for it. All I knew was the title and what the cover looked like. It looks like I'm going to have to do this more often seeing as I really enjoyed this one!<br /><br />This was an enjoyable second chance romance. I have found that second chance romances really aren't my thing but this one worked. I loved how it was written in two parts. You got Nate and Lia's past and then their present. I enjoyed all of the secondary characters along with Nate and Lia. This story was written well and I can't remember really seeing any grammar errors which is a huge turnoff for me when reading. There were some inconsistencies/holes within the story but I worked through them. I understand what the author was trying to do. Or at least I think I do. It seemed to me that she was trying to make sure that the young Lia and Nate were different from the adult Lia and Nate. It didn't fully work but it did work. It was also a tad bit long but I couldn't put it down. I really liked the epilogue and was shocked. I didn't expect it and I really liked it. It sets the next book up, which is about a different character, nicely. <br /><br />Overall, I enjoyed this one and will check out the next in this series.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3906728555983138066" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

