    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1251871126" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1251871126" />
    <a title="Laura" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23713049-laura"><img alt="Laura" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1446916236p2/23713049.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1251871126?book_show_action=true">Apr 11, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Laura" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Laura" href="/user/show/23713049-laura">Laura</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1251871126" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3466223450802045679">This is one of those books that is far from perfect plot wise but strangely addictive. First read for me by this author. I liked the writing style.<br/><br/>The story is in two parts. The first part is when Neil/Nate and Cecelia/Lia meet as 16 year olds. Lia is a completely different book heroine to what I&apos;m used to reading. She is not a shy little virgin. Far from it, her and her two friends have a game they play which is not a nice one. However, when Nate meets her, he is smitten. They start off as frie</span>
  <span id="freeText3466223450802045679" style="display:none">This is one of those books that is far from perfect plot wise but strangely addictive. First read for me by this author. I liked the writing style.<br /><br />The story is in two parts. The first part is when Neil/Nate and Cecelia/Lia meet as 16 year olds. Lia is a completely different book heroine to what I'm used to reading. She is not a shy little virgin. Far from it, her and her two friends have a game they play which is not a nice one. However, when Nate meets her, he is smitten. They start off as friends but it soon turns to more. His mother is not over keen on him having Lia as a girlfriend. Although they are only 16, nearly 17, they fall in love but Lia is worried that Nate is going to give up too much for her so when something from Lia's past dalliances comes to light, Lia makes a decision to end their relationship and then she leaves with no goodbye.<br /><br />The second part of the story is set 14 years later as Lia is approaching her 30th birthday and her best friends have got her tickets to see Nate Kelly, a Country Music star that Lia is obsessed with. Little do her friends know that Nate is the Neil from her past that she has told them about. Now when I got to the second part, I felt like there was quite a lot of 'telling' rather than 'showing' going on. There were two conversations I really wanted to read about but instead we were only told about them. I found it a bit strange which particular 'friend' was still in Lia's life and how close they had become. After what happened in the first part, I didn't think he would still be in the profession he was. There were too many people from the first part that appeared in the second part that I found it a bit unrealistic.<br /><br />As for Nate who was now a Country Music star and covered in tattoos and piercings even though in the first part he did no singing and his songwriting was only mentioned briefly. In the first part he is a Football player, not a singer! I didn't feel the reason for his tattoos and piercings were fully explained. I felt him and Lia reconnected far too quickly without having 'the conversation'. I also felt the thing that Lia had decided age 15 to keep for her husband was also a tad far fetched as was the fact that just by changing her surname when she went to College that Nate was never able to find her. The fact he becomes so successful yet still thinks of her all the time then I'm sure he had people at his disposal that could have tracked her down for him.<br /><br />I liked Nate. I liked him in the first and the second part. He's not a 'bad boy' but in the second part, he has certainly lived the life of a music star. I also liked Mike the best friend to both of them from their past but I never really felt I liked Lia that much. I wasn't sure why most men seemed so enamoured with her! I also wondered how Nate's brother Noah came to feature so heavily in the second part when his name wasn't even mentioned in the first part but I did like his character. Some of the plot just seemed thrown in (her recent ex) and never fully explored. In the second part, Lia is a High School Teacher but for a teacher, she never seemed that responsible to me and I found it strange that became her chosen profession.<br /> <br />I've had a good moan but like I say, it's far from perfect but I couldn't stop reading. It's a long book and I like books that span a good few years. There were some good characters and some I didn't like. The epilogue is told from Mike's POV. I must say, I didn't see that coming what we read about him and I was a bit surprised at that. His book is next and I look forward to seeing who he ends up with. I can see there is scope for quite a few of the characters to have their own stories which I would be interested in reading.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3466223450802045679" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

