<div id="review_1242403498" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1242403498" />
    <a title="Tiffany Readz" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11659152-tiffany-readz"><img alt="Tiffany Readz" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1465912712p2/11659152.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1242403498?book_show_action=true">Mar 31, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tiffany Readz" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tiffany Readz" href="/user/show/11659152-tiffany-readz">Tiffany Readz</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1242403498" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15614480098448864664">This book had me from the blurb and then until the very last page. Rarely do we pass up a hot, tatted up, soulful singer, however getting to know Nate from the beginning was it for me. Carina Adams did a clever thing with this book by starting us in the present, then taking us to the past, then back to the present. Giving her readers every ugly detail of the relationship. <br/><br/>&quot;I couldn&apos;t let him do it, couldn&apos;t let me be the thing that held him back, couldn&apos;t let his love for me destroy his dreams. </span>
  <span id="freeText15614480098448864664" style="display:none">This book had me from the blurb and then until the very last page. Rarely do we pass up a hot, tatted up, soulful singer, however getting to know Nate from the beginning was it for me. Carina Adams did a clever thing with this book by starting us in the present, then taking us to the past, then back to the present. Giving her readers every ugly detail of the relationship. <br /><br />"I couldn't let him do it, couldn't let me be the thing that held him back, couldn't let his love for me destroy his dreams. So I did the only thing I could do; I wrecked it all." ~ Lia (Cecelia)<br /><br />And boy did she. Although Lia let Neil go, she still loves him more than ever. The way she left pretty much sealed the deal, until one night her friends decide to surprise her with tickets and backstage passes to one of his concerts. The past comes rushing back for both of them, along with mountains of baggage as well.<br /><br />For Neil, Lia was the one that got away from him when he was only seventeen. The close relationship with his grandpa made him an old soul and he knew Lia was his forever girl. She was everything he didn't know he wanted, a fiery red head with quick wit to keep him on his toes. Too bad his parents still had some control of his life at that age, so things didn't work out the way he planned.<br /><br />Neil never forgot about his Red, ever. No matter how many girls he went through (Ugh I hated that) and how many songs he wrote, it's still been fourteen years since he's layed eyes on his girl. Seeing her at the meet and greet brought all of those feelings back to the surface, including the hatred he still carries for the way she left him.<br /><br />"Watching her was like seeing your favorite movie again; you knew all the best parts, but you'd forgotten the little things that made it truly great." ~ Neil (Nate)<br /><br />By knowing how they ended up, I couldn't read this book fast enough to see it all come together or fall apart. Carina Adams gives us an epic love story that spans over fourteen years, past and present relationship involvement as well as best friends, band members and family still chipping in their two cents. While Lia and Neil were our main focus, the rest of the supporting characters were written so you actually cared what was going on with them as well. Just when you think you see the cliche set up, the book takes a turn and at 93% you still aren't sure what is going to happen. Great book, great story and I will be waiting for Mike's turn.<br /><br />Reviewed for Renee Entress's Blog<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="15614480098448864664" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


