        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1254558342" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10884201691333661260">Absolutely LOVED this book! It had everything I love in a romance...friends to lovers and 2nd chance romance all in one. I couldn&apos;t put this book down and stayed up way too late and then got up way too early the next day to finish it. LOL. I adored Lea. She was fantastic. She molded into a stigma because of her status in town, but she was such a sweet and loyal person. Nate aka Neil and Lia were fantastic as friends, sweet as can be when they dated in high school and smokin hot together when the</span>
  <span id="freeText10884201691333661260" style="display:none">Absolutely LOVED this book! It had everything I love in a romance...friends to lovers and 2nd chance romance all in one. I couldn't put this book down and stayed up way too late and then got up way too early the next day to finish it. LOL. I adored Lea. She was fantastic. She molded into a stigma because of her status in town, but she was such a sweet and loyal person. Nate aka Neil and Lia were fantastic as friends, sweet as can be when they dated in high school and smokin hot together when they were adults. She was secure in her relationship with Neil and handled difficult situations with grace and trust. Neil was sexy and perfect for Lea. Their chemistry was off the charts but you could also feel the love they had for eachother. Noah was freakin adorable and loved all the band members and Lea's adult friends. This book had me swooning, broken hearted, and rejoicing. It was a wild ride and their HEA was fabulous. Loved it!!</span>
