<div id="review_1401180686" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1401180686" />
    <a title="Rosa Sharon (iScream Book Blog)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16932050-rosa-sharon-iscream-book-blog"><img alt="Rosa Sharon (iScream Book Blog)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1577846465p2/16932050.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1401180686?book_show_action=true">Sep 25, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rosa Sharon (iScream Book Blog)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rosa Sharon (iScream Book Blog)" href="/user/show/16932050-rosa-sharon-iscream-book-blog">Rosa Sharon (iScream Book Blog)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16932050-rosa-sharon-iscream-book-blog?shelf=teacher-student">teacher-student</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16932050-rosa-sharon-iscream-book-blog?shelf=series">series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16932050-rosa-sharon-iscream-book-blog?shelf=standalone">standalone</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16932050-rosa-sharon-iscream-book-blog?shelf=tattoos">tattoos</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16932050-rosa-sharon-iscream-book-blog?shelf=music-lover-alert">music-lover-alert</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16932050-rosa-sharon-iscream-book-blog?shelf=copy-for-review">copy-for-review</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16932050-rosa-sharon-iscream-book-blog?shelf=multiple-pov">multiple-pov</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16932050-rosa-sharon-iscream-book-blog?shelf=sweet">sweet</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/16932050-rosa-sharon-iscream-book-blog?shelf=4-stars">4-stars</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1401180686" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12711040294493150691"><b>My money was on the redhead...</b><br/><br/>Hmm... This was my first Carina Adams read. It was the sexy cover and musical references that caught my attention...and then the blurb closed the deal with <i>
  <b>covered in tattoos</b>
</i>and <i>
  <b>ultimate bad boy.</b>
</i><br/><br/>The Prologue grabbed my attention immediately, and then the author took me back in time to when the main characters met in high school. While I did find this period interesting, it was a little <i>
  <b>too long and detailed</b>
</i> to keep my full attention. I was tempted to ski</span>
  <span id="freeText12711040294493150691" style="display:none"><b>My money was on the redhead...</b><br /><br />Hmm... This was my first Carina Adams read. It was the sexy cover and musical references that caught my attention...and then the blurb closed the deal with <i>
  <b>covered in tattoos</b>
</i>and <i>
  <b>ultimate bad boy.</b>
</i><br /><br />The Prologue grabbed my attention immediately, and then the author took me back in time to when the main characters met in high school. While I did find this period interesting, it was a little <i>
  <b>too long and detailed</b>
</i> to keep my full attention. I was tempted to skim, but was afraid to miss something, so I persevered. The second half of the book was a page turner. It skipped quite a few years and then jumped right into right now. I was kinda frustrated that the front was so heavy, and the middle was missing, but the end more than made up for it.<br /><br />Once I got to meet the other band members of the Bama Boys, I was a happy reader. Their personalities had me hooked right away. I was ready to sign on as roady just to hang around them. Their humor and antics were very entertaining. I really enjoyed the tour bus, backstage, concert, social media and other music industry details. I connected with Lia's girlfriends and appreciated their loyalty and support for her. And then there was the evil bitches that did the opposite. The entitled, rich, stuckup women that wanted Nate for themselves and referred to Lia as being trailerhood trash had me very riled up.<br /><br />Nate had my heart from the beginning, but I didn't give him a free pass. He pissed me off at times, but then I had to remind myself that he was just a teenager. He had so many lessons left to learn, the hard way. I tried to counsel him. I told him that those women were manipulating him. I warned him he was gonna be sorry if he didn't listen to me. But as usual, the characters never do...smh. I had to bite my nails and suffer through the suspense of waiting for the fur to fly and the dust to settle. I had to watch my girl walk away. I had to witness their heartbreak, and share in their suffering.<br /><br />I was totally invested by the end. I was ranting and railing. Guessing and gasping. Waiting and wondering. Sniffling and smiling. And now, I'm ready for more Bama Boys...especially Mike. That big musclebound beefcake has my heart. I want him to find the happiness he deserves, and I can't wait to meet her. Or...will I be seeing her again? Hmmm? Have I already met her?</span>
  <a data-text-id="12711040294493150691" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


