<div id="review_2690027267" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2690027267" />
    <a title="Ellie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/56464293-ellie"><img alt="Ellie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1551277899p2/56464293.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2690027267?book_show_action=true">Feb 03, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ellie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ellie" href="/user/show/56464293-ellie">Ellie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/25333776-forever-red">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer2690027267&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2690027267" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9535440991284067336">2.5 stars. The second half didn&apos;t live up to the first. Inconsistencies and missed details in key parts of the plot and in character development. There was a handful of jumps where telling was chosen over showing the story unfold.<br/>The first part was engaging and interesting, with a good build toward some sort of climax, and the setup was there for a satisfying second half, which picks up about 13 years after part one ends. However, part two failed to deliver. The characters were too different to </span>
  <span id="freeText9535440991284067336" style="display:none">2.5 stars. The second half didn't live up to the first. Inconsistencies and missed details in key parts of the plot and in character development. There was a handful of jumps where telling was chosen over showing the story unfold.<br />The first part was engaging and interesting, with a good build toward some sort of climax, and the setup was there for a satisfying second half, which picks up about 13 years after part one ends. However, part two failed to deliver. The characters were too different to chalk it up to 'character development.' Neil/Nate and Red/Lia went from likable, intriguing high school kids to a generic, alpha as*hole and a wishy-washy doormat. The second half played out thus:<br />Haven't seen one another in over a decade? Have sex<br />Need closure to move on? Have sex.<br />Need to talk things out? Have sex.<br />Had an argument? Have sex.<br />Been too busy to spend time together? Have sex<br />Break up for weeks over a stupid misunderstanding and need to work things out? Have sex.<br />One line kind of summed it all up and that was along the lines of all the missed time and problems they faced could be fixed 'in the bedroom.'<br />Yeah, no.<br />Seriously lame and boring. I don't care how differently the words are rearranged, a long sex scene with too much detail is still a long sex scene with too much detail and is a poor substitute for good storytelling. Which this writer is absolutely capable of so why they took the cheap and lazy route is beyond me. But whatever.<br />I didn't expect to be underwhelmed by this book given the solid start, but it didn't deliver. It wasn't awful, just forgettable.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9535440991284067336" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


