        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1257398885" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13686551771175627421">An average enjoyable read that fell short of what I had hoped would be something a bit different and extraspecial. Loved the cover and it gets kudos for drawing my attention.<br/><br/>Told in dual POVs helped to give the story much more depth and staying power than otherwise would have been found. There was a bounce in time frames with teen years and characters from opposite sides of the tracks into adulthood some ten years later for a nice balance in the second chance at love storyline. One has become a </span>
  <span id="freeText13686551771175627421" style="display:none">An average enjoyable read that fell short of what I had hoped would be something a bit different and extraspecial. Loved the cover and it gets kudos for drawing my attention.<br /><br />Told in dual POVs helped to give the story much more depth and staying power than otherwise would have been found. There was a bounce in time frames with teen years and characters from opposite sides of the tracks into adulthood some ten years later for a nice balance in the second chance at love storyline. One has become a famous country singer and they reconnect by a chance encounter.<br /><br />The ending seemed too rushed and lacked the oomph I was anticipating. And the Epilogue, which could have saved it all, was more of a teaser for what may be Mike's book, but no date for a release is in sight which made it appear more of a cliffhanger ending. Not good in my opinion.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13686551771175627421" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


