<div id="review_1238097644" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1238097644" />
    <a title="Theresa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10601284-theresa"><img alt="Theresa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1558026273p2/10601284.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1238097644?book_show_action=true">Mar 26, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Theresa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Theresa" href="/user/show/10601284-theresa">Theresa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1238097644" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14308260011106753742">Nate and Lia are high school sweethearts. Through circumstances, they separate and move forward in different directions. Both are broken-hearted, but life must go on. Nate becomes a famous country music superstar. Lia follows his career, and is very proud of the man he has become.<br/><br/>Lia’s friends decide to surprise her for her birthday with concert tickets and backstage passes to see the one and only Nate Kelly. Her friends have no idea that Lia knows Nate Kelly personally—and she’s terrified at th</span>
  <span id="freeText14308260011106753742" style="display:none">Nate and Lia are high school sweethearts. Through circumstances, they separate and move forward in different directions. Both are broken-hearted, but life must go on. Nate becomes a famous country music superstar. Lia follows his career, and is very proud of the man he has become.<br /><br />Lia’s friends decide to surprise her for her birthday with concert tickets and backstage passes to see the one and only Nate Kelly. Her friends have no idea that Lia knows Nate Kelly personally—and she’s terrified at the thought of seeing him after all these years.<br /><br />Nate has worked hard to attain his success, and he definitely enjoys the spoils of it. Women want to be with him, and guys want to hang out with him. When Nate sees Lia backstage at his concert, he’s dumbstruck. He can’t believe that Lia is there right in front of him. He hasn’t seen or heard from her in 12 years—and he’s at a loss.<br /><br />You can’t help but fall in love with Nate and Lia. He is a beautiful man with an old-school soul. He’s never forgotten his roots, and with his close friends and family supporting him, they help keep him grounded. I can’t get more specific without spoilers, but trust me, he’s a heart stopper! Lia is a strong-willed young lady, not afraid to speak her mind. She is smart, and has a plan to get away from her town once she graduates high school.<br /><br />It starts with Nate and Lia in high school, and follows their growth into adulthood, and showing how decisions made as a teenager affected not only them as adults, but their friends and family, as well. <br /><br />The secondary characters are so much a part of this story, it’s almost like an ensemble cast of people you’d love to know—well, most of them. They have depth, and they keep you on your toes. Nate’s band members are like frat brothers, and they are hilarious. You feel you know all of them personally, and Carina makes you feel like you’re right there with them every step of the way. A testament to her talent as a writer.<br /><br />I went through a range of emotions with this book. I love how Carina tells this complicated love story in such a way, that by the end, you realize it couldn’t have happened any other way. I would love to see this continue into a series, and I know I won’t be the only one once readers get a hold of this book.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="14308260011106753742" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


