<div id="review_1250903492" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1250903492" />
    <a title="E.J. Fechenda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12780124-e-j-fechenda"><img alt="E.J. Fechenda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442885023p2/12780124.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1250903492?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="E.J. Fechenda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="E.J. Fechenda" href="/user/show/12780124-e-j-fechenda">E.J. Fechenda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1250903492" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14971148011146017681">From first love to forever love and all the fears, angst and passion that happens in between...this book has it all. <br/><br/>One of the things I&apos;ve noticed is that Carina apparently enjoys putting her characters through the emotional wringer and this story isn&apos;t any different. Lia is a stubborn, fiery redhead with a questionable social status and reputation when Neil Kelly transfers to her high school. Neil&apos;s different; he doesn&apos;t know of her history and even though he lives on the wealthy side of town </span>
  <span id="freeText14971148011146017681" style="display:none">From first love to forever love and all the fears, angst and passion that happens in between...this book has it all. <br /><br />One of the things I've noticed is that Carina apparently enjoys putting her characters through the emotional wringer and this story isn't any different. Lia is a stubborn, fiery redhead with a questionable social status and reputation when Neil Kelly transfers to her high school. Neil's different; he doesn't know of her history and even though he lives on the wealthy side of town and quickly becomes a star on the football team, he doesn't care that she comes from a humble background. He totally gets her and they have an undeniable connection. Sounds perfect, right? It is until Lia gets scared. <br /><br />This is understandable. Love can be scary - in fact it can be terrifying and complicated - just like high school. Carina puts the reader front row and center to watch their relationship unfurl then unravel. Fast forward over ten years and we find that Lia and Neil (now the famous Nate Kelly) are still worlds apart. They have a second chance, but can they move past their past (and out of their own way) to make a future together? <br /><br />The character development in Forever Red is fantastic as we get to know Lia and Neil as high school students and then again as adults. Carina introduces us to a whole cast of characters, from parents and friends (don't get me started on Nate's mother), who add dimension to the riveting story. Be prepared to hunker down as you won't be able to stop reading once you start. <br /><br />* I received an ARC in exchange for an honest review * <br /> </span>
  <a data-text-id="14971148011146017681" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


