<div id="review_1271908088" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1271908088" />
    <a title="Dayreader Reviews" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16114709-dayreader-reviews"><img alt="Dayreader Reviews" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1431395284p2/16114709.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1271908088?book_show_action=true">May 04, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dayreader Reviews" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dayreader Reviews" href="/user/show/16114709-dayreader-reviews">Dayreader Reviews</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1271908088" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10600020963211965614">This was my first experience reading a book by Carina Adams and I wasn&apos;t disappointed! I love the cover of Forever Red. It drew me in and made me want to know more.<br/>The story begins with Lia&apos;s friends taking her to a Nate Kelly concert, in a limousine, as a surprise birthday gift. They also manage to secure passes for a meet and greet, all without knowing that Nate Kelly, the king of country music, was her first love when they were in high school. In the years since, they have had no contact but </span>
  <span id="freeText10600020963211965614" style="display:none">This was my first experience reading a book by Carina Adams and I wasn't disappointed! I love the cover of Forever Red. It drew me in and made me want to know more.<br />The story begins with Lia's friends taking her to a Nate Kelly concert, in a limousine, as a surprise birthday gift. They also manage to secure passes for a meet and greet, all without knowing that Nate Kelly, the king of country music, was her first love when they were in high school. In the years since, they have had no contact but they both still have feelings for each other.<br />This beautiful, emotional read was difficult for me to read at times because Carina made me so heartbroken for them. There is a lot of hurt between them over decisions that Lia made in the past, that ended their relationship. These decisions weren't the best choices, but she made them out of love for Nate and with the best of intentions.<br />I absolutely loved reading this book and I know I will be rereading it at some point because it's just that good! I can't wait for the next book in the series where we get Mike's story. I came to love all of the supporting characters so much I feel as if I know them all!<br />This is a second chance romance that will tear at your heartstrings, so get your tissues ready and enjoy! I'm giving this beautiful story 5 stars!</span>
  <a data-text-id="10600020963211965614" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


