<div id="review_1256345508" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1256345508" />
    <a title="Tammy Hamilton Green" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26004045-tammy-hamilton-green"><img alt="Tammy Hamilton Green" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442498391p2/26004045.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1256345508?book_show_action=true">Apr 16, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tammy Hamilton Green" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tammy Hamilton Green" href="/user/show/26004045-tammy-hamilton-green">Tammy Hamilton Green</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1256345508" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16688853034062293643">This story hooks you pretty fast and keeps you on the edge of your seat waiting to learn what happens next. There&apos;s plenty of sexual tension, story angst and really comical moments. I love the rocker genre, but I didn&apos;t even realize this was what I was going to be reading with this one. In fact, if there was one thing that bothered me about this book is that despite Nate/Neil&apos;s family history, he jumped from football stand out to rock star status without so much as picking up a guitar. I had no </span>
  <span id="freeText16688853034062293643" style="display:none">This story hooks you pretty fast and keeps you on the edge of your seat waiting to learn what happens next. There's plenty of sexual tension, story angst and really comical moments. I love the rocker genre, but I didn't even realize this was what I was going to be reading with this one. In fact, if there was one thing that bothered me about this book is that despite Nate/Neil's family history, he jumped from football stand out to rock star status without so much as picking up a guitar. I had no idea his intention was to follow in his family's legendary footsteps. That kind of stuck with me and with some, even to a small degree reference or story to help me with that transition, I would have given this a 5-star review. <br /><br />The writer tells a tale of 2 love struck teens who would sacrifice it all for the other, even being together. There's the ex's constantly in their face, messing with their happiness and you can't forget how nasty his Mom was to her. Lia is no innocent. Her trailer trash reputation and naughty school girl games, catch up with her, despite her efforts to do it right with Neil. Sometimes a love that transcends years apart is so strong it's meant to be inked FOREVER RED. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16688853034062293643" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


