<div id="review_1247247396" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1247247396" />
    <a title="Carri Frechette" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/33115591-carri-frechette"><img alt="Carri Frechette" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1405525436p2/33115591.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1247247396?book_show_action=true">Apr 06, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Carri Frechette" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Carri Frechette" href="/user/show/33115591-carri-frechette">Carri Frechette</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1247247396" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10483581616426252884">I was gifted an ARC of Forever Red in exchange for an honest review. <br/><br/>Forever Red had me hooked from beginning to end. Nate/Neil and Lia heat up the pages in this friends-to-lovers story about second chances and forgiveness. I loved how the book started in present-day, but brought me back to their first high school encounter, the romantic relationship that followed, and, the falling out that happened between the two. Flash forward to present day: Nate is now the hottest country singer in the land</span>
  <span id="freeText10483581616426252884" style="display:none">I was gifted an ARC of Forever Red in exchange for an honest review. <br /><br />Forever Red had me hooked from beginning to end. Nate/Neil and Lia heat up the pages in this friends-to-lovers story about second chances and forgiveness. I loved how the book started in present-day, but brought me back to their first high school encounter, the romantic relationship that followed, and, the falling out that happened between the two. Flash forward to present day: Nate is now the hottest country singer in the land. After a chance meeting with Lia and her girlfriends at one of his concerts, old feelings resurface. Can they make it work this time around? Only time will tell. I absolutely loved most of the supporting characters (with the exception of a couple, whose teeth I wanted to knock out of their snotty little heads) in the book as well. I would love to see books come out with Mike and Noah’s stories, as well – hint, hint, hint ;) Also, as just a little side note: I grew up and went to school in the same area as the author, so I found the fact that she referred to a couple of places that are still here in our area very cool! <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10483581616426252884" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


